profile:
Scott Ballantyne saw the need in the renovation market for an online shopping tool for countertops. Living in Brooklin for 10 years, Scott knew the hassle it was having to drive into the west end of Toronto every time he needed renovation supplies. With over 25 years in the home and commercial renovation industry, Scott noticed the niche and wanted to provide people within the GTA with an easier way to shop for countertops. Scott has specialized in kitchen and bathroom renovations for the past seven years and is also certified with IICRC in Insurance restoration.

Durhamcountertops.com is a quality, shop-at-home service for solid surface countertops and custom backsplashes. However, the website is more than just an online shopping site. Scott provides other renovation advice and services such as the removal and disposal of your old countertops as well as sink and faucet installation.

“I enjoy helping people through the entire renovation process,” says Scott. “Renovating a home is a stressful time for most people and I understand that a contractor needs to be sensitive and aware of the clients needs.”

Durhamcountertops.com will even bring over 75  different stone products both natural and man-made, directly to your home so that you may see them in their actual surroundings. Scott will bring to life your ideas by creating a computerized template that is taken directly to the fabrication facility, so that what you have ordered in your home will be exactly what the final product will look like.

Living and working in Brooklin was no accident for Scott. Having strong ties to his community has always been important to him. Having the opportunity to work in his hometown and provide Brooklin residents with high-quality, accessible and affordable service is Scott’s number one priority. Countertops that we specialize in include Granite, Marble, & Quartz Countertops.  We serve Durham, Pickering, Ajax, Whitby, Oshawa and surrounding area.
